<item>
            <title>[OAK-1293] MongoNodeBuilder does not track base state properly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1293</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As mentioned in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1288&quot; title=&quot;NPE when running SmallFileReadTest on mongo&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-1288&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-1288&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; the base state in MongoNodeBuilder is not tracked properly. The method getBaseState() must also detect base state changes on the root builder and re-fetch its base state similar to how KernelNodeBuilder is implemented.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
